    "explanation": "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrj9iz0m/7bca26af-8ec0-472a-8d32-6f018c1409e6/9b4dd660-b607-11ee-ad4f-310a26465ac9/file-6y3zli1lrj9iz0n.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrj9iz0m/7bca26af-8ec0-472a-8d32-6f018c1409e6/9b4dd660-b607-11ee-ad4f-310a26465ac9/file-6y3zli1lrj9iz0n.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 8 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>bond has the most single bond character in compound II followed by I and II respectively.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1lrj9jo1d/bdf9dd98-1bcf-40b8-91f7-2a08fd04470f/aea1ce10-b607-11ee-ad4f-310a26465ac9/file-6y3zli1lrj9jo1e.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1lrj9jo1d/bdf9dd98-1bcf-40b8-91f7-2a08fd04470f/aea1ce10-b607-11ee-ad4f-310a26465ac9/file-6y3zli1lrj9jo1e.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"WB JEE 2023 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 8 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>Thus, the order is II &gt; I &gt; III.</p>",
