    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "<p>The correct order of boiling points of given compounds is $$\\mathrm{II}<\\mathrm{I}<\\mathrm{III}$$.</p>\n<p>Butan-2-ol shows stronger hydrogen bonding than N-ethylethanamine. While ethoxyethane have dipole association which is weaker than hydrogen bonding. Thus, the order followed is</p> <p>ethoxyethane < N-ethylethanamine < butan-2-ol.</p>",
