  {
    "direction": null,
    "content": "Among Me<sub>3</sub>N, C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N and MeCN (Me = methyl group) the electronegativity of N is in the order",
    "options": [
      {
        "identifier": "A",
        "content": "MeCN &gt; C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N &gt; Me<sub>3</sub>N"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "B",
        "content": "C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N &gt; Me<sub>3</sub>N &gt; MeCN"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "C",
        "content": "Me<sub>3</sub>N &gt; MeCN &gt; C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N"
      },
      {
        "identifier": "D",
        "content": "Electronegativity same in all"
      }
    ],
    "correct_options": [
      "A"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "$$\\because$$ In Me<sub>3</sub>N $$\\to$$ N is sp<sup>3</sup> -hybrid<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l92zpnfc/abf24c68-8dc2-4d08-b4cd-636430c19cbf/ca830580-48b8-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zpnfd.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l92zpnfc/abf24c68-8dc2-4d08-b4cd-636430c19cbf/ca830580-48b8-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zpnfd.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2017 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 16 English Explanation 1\"><br>In C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N $$\\to$$ N is sp<sup>2</sup> -hybrid<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l92zq6ed/c3ef61c5-7d55-41c4-a180-0372aee0c243/d92b0150-48b8-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zq6ee.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l92zq6ed/c3ef61c5-7d55-41c4-a180-0372aee0c243/d92b0150-48b8-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zq6ee.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2017 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 16 English Explanation 2\"><br>and in MeCN $$\\to$$ N is sp -hybrid<br><br>Also electronegativity of any element $$\\alpha$$% s-character in hybrid orbitals.<br><br>Thus, order of electronegativity for nitrogen is <br><br>MeCN &gt; C<sub>5</sub>H<sub>5</sub>N &lt; Me<sub>3</sub>N",
