    "correct_options": [
      "C"
    ],
    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "$$\\because$$ In p-nitrobenzoic acid (Z) $$-$$ NO<sub>2</sub> present as electron withdrawing group, thus is most acidic<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l92zxsdq/5711afe2-4873-406e-9108-8dcd62f37c8f/acd010e0-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zxsdr.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l92zxsdq/5711afe2-4873-406e-9108-8dcd62f37c8f/acd010e0-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zxsdr.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2017 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 17 English Explanation 1\"><br>(X) $$\\because$$ Benzoic acid is stabilised via resonance, thus is more acidic than per oxybenzoic acid.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l92zycdj/6d631c6a-2cab-4f56-89f7-d864e00cccc0/bc421370-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zycdk.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l92zycdj/6d631c6a-2cab-4f56-89f7-d864e00cccc0/bc421370-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zycdk.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2017 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 17 English Explanation 2\"><br>(Y) peroxy benzoic acid does not show any such resonance.<br><br><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/1l92zz1wo/5999c2f7-8a88-49d2-8413-68701a6b1814/cffb0e80-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zz1wp.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/1l92zz1wo/5999c2f7-8a88-49d2-8413-68701a6b1814/cffb0e80-48b9-11ed-b666-33bcf3c9cb83/file-1l92zz1wp.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0px auto;max-height:40vh\" alt=\"WB JEE 2017 Chemistry - General Organic Chemistry Question 17 English Explanation 3\"><br>Thus is least acidic.<br><br>Hence, correct order is Z &gt; X &gt; Y.",
