    "answer": null,
    "explanation": "The correct order is 2 &lt; 1 &lt; 3 &lt; 4. Since, more the number of 2$$^\\circ$$ $$-$$ NH $$-$$ group, more is the basic nature.<br><br>(i) Thus, 3 and 4 are more basic than 1 and 2.<br><br>(ii) Between 3 and 4, 4 has one two $$-$$NH<sub>2</sub> group while 3 has only one $$-$$NH<sub>2</sub> group.<br><br>$$\\therefore$$ 4 is more basic than 3.<br><br>(iii) Between 1 and 2, 1 has one $$-$$NH<sub>2</sub> group with no resonance, thus is more basic than 2.",
